## Phase 3 — GSAP Sidebar Animation (REQ-MOB-003)

### TASK-06 — Create `useMobileSheetAnimation` hook

**Requirement:** REQ-MOB-003  
**File:** `src/hooks/use-mobile-sheet-animation.ts` (new)  
**Type:** Create

**What to produce:**
A custom React hook that orchestrates GSAP slide-in/out animations for a mobile sidebar sheet.

**Signature:**
```ts
import { RefObject } from "react";

interface UseMobileSheetAnimationOptions {
  duration?: number;        // default 0.35
  ease?: string;            // default "power3.out"
  reducedMotion?: boolean;  // auto-detected if omitted
}

interface UseMobileSheetAnimationReturn {
  animateOpen: () => void;
  animateClose: () => Promise<void>;
  isAnimating: boolean;
}

export function useMobileSheetAnimation(
  sidebarRef: RefObject<HTMLElement | null>,
  backdropRef: RefObject<HTMLElement | null>,
  options?: UseMobileSheetAnimationOptions
): UseMobileSheetAnimationReturn;
```

**Behavior:**
- `animateOpen`: slides sidebar from `translateX(-100%)` to `translateX(0%)`, fades backdrop from `opacity: 0` to `opacity: 1`.
- `animateClose`: reverses the above; returns a Promise that resolves when GSAP timeline completes.
- `isAnimating`: true while any GSAP timeline is active.
- Respects `prefers-reduced-motion`: if true, skip translation and only toggle opacity instantly (duration 0.01s).
- Cleans up all GSAP tweens on unmount to prevent memory leaks.
- Uses `gsap.fromTo` for bidirectional control.
- Does NOT read layout properties during animation (no layout thrashing).

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Hook file exists at `src/hooks/use-mobile-sheet-animation.ts`.
- [ ] `animateOpen` / `animateClose` run without runtime errors when refs are attached to DOM elements.
- [ ] Animation duration is ≤ 400ms (snappy mobile feel).
- [ ] When `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` is enabled, animation is instant (opacity only).
- [ ] Hook cleans up pending tweens on unmount (no console warnings from GSAP).
- [ ] TypeScript exports the interface and function with correct types.

**Dependencies:** None (pure hook; GSAP is already installed).

