## Phase 4 — Touch Target Accessibility (WCAG 2.2) (REQ-MOB-004)

### TASK-08 — WCAG 2.2 accessibility pass on sidebar and tab components

**Requirement:** REQ-MOB-004  
**Files:**
- `src/components/dashboard/Sidebar.tsx`
- `src/components/admin/NavRow.tsx`
- `src/components/chain/ChainDashboard.tsx`
- `src/components/chain/mobile-tab-pills.tsx`

**Type:** Modify (cross-cutting)

**What to change:**
- **Target size:** Verify every interactive element (links, buttons, tabs) is at least 24×24px (WCAG 2.2 minimum) and ideally 44×44px on mobile. Address any violations found.
- **Focus indicators:** Add visible focus rings (`focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-gold/60 focus-visible:outline-none`) to all custom tappable elements that lack them (sidebar links, NavRow, tab pills, ChainDashboard mobile sidebar buttons).
- **Color + shape:** Ensure active states are not communicated by color alone; confirm existing background/shadow differentiation is present.
- **Touch-action:** Add `touch-manipulation` to all mobile-exclusive buttons to suppress 300ms double-tap delay.
- **Landmarks / roles:** Confirm `role="tablist"` / `role="tab"` on tab pills, `aria-label` on nav containers, and `aria-current="page"` on active nav links.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] axe-core scan on `/dashboard` and `/cadena` shows 0 violations for "target-size" (WCAG 2.2 AA).
- [ ] Tab key navigation shows a visible focus ring on every interactive element in the mobile sidebar and tab bar.
- [ ] No element has `touch-action: auto` on a mobile-exclusive button (should be `touch-manipulation`).
- [ ] Active nav item is programmatically determinable (`aria-current="page"` or `aria-selected="true"`).

**Dependencies:** TASK-01, TASK-02, TASK-03, TASK-04, TASK-05.

